  "notes": [
    "R1 (~8 kohm) and R2 (~0.12 kohm) are the integrated Darlington bias resistors read from the Equivalent Circuit on page 1, given as approximate values; captured with guarantee: typical.",
    "thermal_resistance_junction_case (RthetaJC) is NOT tabulated in this datasheet - only collector dissipation (65 W at TC=25 degC, 2 W at TA=25 degC) and TJ(max)=150 degC are given - so it is omitted rather than back-computed from PD and TJ.",
    "clamp_diode_forward_voltage omitted: the Equivalent Circuit shows only R1/R2; no integral collector-emitter clamp-diode forward voltage is tabulated for this device.",
    "ICEO is 0.5 mA (5e-4 A) at VCE=30 V, IB=0 per the Electrical Characteristics table (the registered brief value of 2e-3 A was not confirmed and was corrected to the datasheet figure).",
    "Cob (output capacitance) is specified as a maximum of 200 pF (2e-10 F), recorded as value.max.",
    "emitter_base_cutoff_current (IEBO, max 2 mA at VEB=5 V) was added from the datasheet in addition to the requested parameter list.",
    "The onsemi document (Publication Order Number TIP122/D, November-2017 Rev.2) was confirmed against the DigiKey-hosted mirror of the onsemi PDF (SHA-256 686c2f6cd9847407dd42d82045b0153433f76ef2b6f2bc8307196a48d0eb4862); onsemi.com blocked a direct fetch (HTTP 403), so datasheetSha256 of the canonical sourceUrl bytes is omitted rather than asserted from a different file."
  ]
